(116, 2, '2020-09-13 09:59:08', '2020-09-13 09:59:08', '<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SECTOR</td><td>PROPOSED PROGRAMS/ PROJECTS</td><td>LOCATION</td><td>YEAR OF IMPLEMENTATION</td><td>IMPLEMENTING AGENCY</td></tr><tr><td>A. SOCIAL SERVICES</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>1. Education</td><td>To rehabilitate all the&nbsp; school buildings in need of repair by the end of the planning period &nbsp; To provide centralized elementary schools with modern teaching equipment. &nbsp; To allocate funds for the training of school teachers and other school personnel &nbsp; To convert selected and appropriate buildings to much needed facilities as laboratories and clinics for all schools &nbsp; To establish libraries or reading centers in schools without the facility &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Poblacion &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide</td><td>Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning Period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period</td><td>LGU, Concerned agencies, DepEd &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DepEd &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DepEd &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DepEd &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DepEd</td></tr><tr><td>2. Health</td><td>To reduce morbidity and mortality rates of infectious diseases. &nbsp; To decrease the number of malnourished children by 100% &nbsp; &nbsp; To provide&nbsp; barangay health centers in all barangays &nbsp; &nbsp; To upgrade existing health centers in terms of personnel, medicines and equipment &nbsp; &nbsp; To develop the municipal dumpsite including its access road, facilities &nbsp; &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; San Miguel</td><td>Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; First half of planning period</td><td>LGU, Concerned Agencies, DOH &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, DOH &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, DOH &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, DOH &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, DOH, DENR</td></tr><tr><td>3. HousingousingHousing</td><td>To cut down the housing backlog through construction of affordable housing units and renovation of dilapidated units &nbsp; To help make subdivision housing available to more people &nbsp;</td><td>Poblacion, San Miguel &nbsp; Poblacion, San Miguel, Concerned barangays &nbsp;</td><td>First half of planning period &nbsp; Planning Period</td><td>LGU, Concerned agencies &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies</td></tr><tr><td>4. Social Welfare</td><td>To deliver basic services and improve social well-being of 60% of each of the different sectoral clienteles &nbsp; To establish a day care center in all the different barangays &nbsp; &nbsp; To improve the nutritional status &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; To decrease unemployment thru livelihood opportunities &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide</td><td>First half of planning period &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; First three years of planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; First half of planning period</td><td>LGU, Concerned Agencies, DSWD &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, DSWD &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, DSWD, DOH &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, DSWD, DOLE</td></tr><tr><td>5. Protective Services</td><td>To increase the PNP and BFP manpower to meet existing minimum standards &nbsp; To provide support funds for the protective services sector &nbsp; &nbsp; To conduct regular and periodic training, community law enforcement, crime prevention, and calamity/disaster preparedness for Civilian Volunteer Organizations (CVOs) &nbsp; &nbsp; To involve the Disaster Coordinating Council, NGOs, barangay elders, and other concerned sectors in support of the PNP, BFP, and CVOs in the civic responsibility of community protection during periods of crisis &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Poblacion &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide</td><td>First three years of planning period &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period</td><td>LGU, PNP &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, PNP &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, PNP, DILG &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies, PNP, DILG &nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>6. Sports and Recreation</td><td>To upgrade all&nbsp; existing sports and recreational facilities by the end of the planning period &nbsp; To repackage open spaces and sports and recreation areas for tourism outdoor activities based on a tourism plan &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide</td><td>Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period</td><td>LGU, Concerned Agencies &nbsp; LGU, Concerned Agencies</td></tr><tr><td>B. ECONOMIC</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>1. Agriculture</td><td>To increase the average yield of palay of in irrigated areas and rain-fed areas by 50% during the whole planning period &nbsp; To prepare a comprehensive agricultural master plan identifying the best suitable and profitable crops in all barangays, particularly in the barangays of Concordia, Sapa Grande and SapaPequena by the first year of the planning period &nbsp; To prepare a plan for livestock production and marketing in the first year of the planning period<em></em> &nbsp; &nbsp; To prepare a special plan for the management of pasturelands and open spaces, in connection with tourism plans, within the first year of the planning period<em></em> &nbsp; &nbsp; To declare unclassified forests as protected forests and prepare a forest management plan for the municipality within the first year of the planning period<em></em> &nbsp; To expand the coverage of the livestock breeding and dispersal program by the first three (3) years of the planning period. &nbsp; To increase poultry production by 100% in the whole planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; To rehabilitate more farm-to-market roads up to the year 2018 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; To construct and install facilities for communal irrigation systems in irrigated barangays and expand irrigable areas &nbsp; &nbsp; To provide enough multi-purpose drying pavements and construct farm post-harvest facilities within 3 years of the planning period <em>&nbsp;</em> &nbsp;</td><td>Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Concerned barangays &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Municipality-wide &nbsp;</td><td>Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; First year of planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; First year of planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; First year of planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; First year of planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; First three years of planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2018 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Planning period &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Within three years of planning period</td><td>LGU, Concerned agencies, DA &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA, DENR &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA, DPWH &nbsp; &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA, DPWH &nbsp; LGU, Concerned agencies, DA &nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>2. Commerce and Industry</td><td>To designate Poblacion and Pogoroac as commercial centers and prepare a special commercial plan for these areas<em></em> &nbsp; &nbsp;