 and high value crops</li><li>To increase the productivity and income of marginal farmers</li><li>To ensure the productivity of agricultural resources over the long-term</li><li>To increase market access and develop seasonal markets</li><li>To increase access to modern agricultural technology and production schemes</li><li>To strengthen agro-based farmers’ cooperatives in terms of management and entrepreneurial capabilities</li><li>To establish an agro-industrial development assistance program</li><li>To strengthen the present technical capability and communication skills of DA and extension workers</li><li>To provide technical training on crop, livestock, and fish production</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2.2. Commerce and Industry</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>To expand physical infrastructure for commerce and trade</li><li>To establish transport routes to municipal and provincial destinations to facilitate trade</li><li>To improve the quality of goods and services and the competitiveness of local resources</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2.3. Infrastructure and Tourism</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>To widen and expand the existing road network and linkages</li><li>To improve the poor physical conditions of stretches of the provincial and barangay road, and to work for their proper maintenance by requesting concerned agencies for the regular allotment of funds, and the inclusion of said roads in the DPWH programs</li><li>To increase the safety factor for people and property on all roads in the municipality</li><li>To efficiently distribute potable water to the various barangays within the municipality</li><li>To improve water quality, and the reliability of water distribution</li><li>To reduce the incidence of water-borne diseases, and promote health and sanitation through the provision of safe water supply</li><li>To ensure 