ntial commercial centers</li><li>Provide funds for the improvement of the existing public market and its annexes</li><li>Improve market and business tax collection and revenue raising schemes for reinvestment into commercial sector infrastructure</li><li>Provide entrepreneurial and business management training for local residents and set up trade fairs</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.3. Infrastructure and Tourism</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Exercise vigilance and care in all major intersections and trunk lines in order to keep roads and passageways safe for both life and property.</li><li>Acquisition of water rights, and seeking professional consultations with the Local Water Utilities Authority on water resources management.</li><li>Upgrade and modernize the power supply distribution facilities in the municipality.</li><li>Monitor and /or maintain the performance of existing facilities.</li><li>Unite tourism plans agriculture and commercial plans</li><li>Revitalize beach tourism in coastal barangay</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.4. Social Services</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Elementary and secondary school facilities should be made accessible to all</li><li>Teacher training registration fees should be allocated from the Educational Support Fund (ESF)</li><li>Items for security guards especially for the National High Schools should be allocated from the ESF</li><li>The distribution of the ESF to public schools should be on a per capita basis and all school heads should be given the opportunity to identify their priority targets</li><li>Municipal government-owned lots used as school sites should be transferred to the Department of Education</li><li>Coordinate with the Technical Education and Skills Development Authority (TESDA) and the Commission on Higher Education (CHED) for the immediate establishment o